  <h1>Phase 1: Foundation Obedience (Weeks 1-8)</h1>

  <div class="alert alert-info">
    <strong>üéØ Objective:</strong> Establish reliable basic commands in low-distraction environments
  </div>

  <h2>Essential Commands</h2>

  <article class="command-card">
    <header>
      <h3>1. Name Recognition</h3>
      <span class="difficulty-badge low">Foundation</span>
    </header>
    <section>
      <p><strong>Goal:</strong> Gypsy turns attention to you within 1 second of hearing her name</p>

      <details open>
        <summary><strong>Training Method</strong></summary>
        <ol>
          <li>Say her name once in a happy, upbeat tone</li>
          <li>The instant she looks at you, mark with "Yes!"</li>
          <li>Reward immediately with treat and praise</li>
          <li>Practice 20-30 repetitions daily in 3-5 minute sessions</li>
        </ol>
      </details>

      <details>
        <summary><strong>Pro Tips for Pitbulls</strong></summary>
        <ul>
          <li>Use high-value treats - pitbulls are very food motivated</li>
          <li>Keep sessions short and fun - their enthusiasm is high</li>
          <li>Never repeat her name - say it once and wait</li>
          <li>Practice in different rooms to generalize</li>
        </ul>
      </details>
    </section>
  </article>

  <article class="command-card">
    <header>
      <h3>2. Sit</h3>
      <span class="difficulty-badge low">Foundation</span>
    </header>
    <section>
      <p><strong>Goal:</strong> Sits within 2 seconds on verbal cue or hand signal</p>

      <details open>
        <summary><strong>Training Method</strong></summary>
        <ol>
          <li>Hold treat at Gypsy's nose level</li>
          <li>Slowly move treat up and back over her head</li>
          <li>As her bottom touches the ground, mark "Yes!"</li>
          <li>Reward immediately</li>
          <li>Add verbal cue "Sit" once she's reliably following the lure</li>
        </ol>
      </details>

      <details>
        <summary><strong>Duration Build Progression</strong></summary>
        <table class="progression-table">
          <tr><th>Week</th><th>Duration</th><th>Success Criteria</th></tr>
          <tr><td>1-2</td><td>3 seconds</td><td>Holds position without fidgeting</td></tr>
          <tr><td>3-4</td><td>10 seconds</td><td>Maintains sit with mild distractions</td></tr>
          <tr><td>5-6</td><td>30 seconds</td><td>Calm and focused</td></tr>
          <tr><td>7-8</td><td>2 minutes</td><td>Completely settled</td></tr>
        </table>
      </details>
    </section>
  </article>

  <h2>Training Principles for Pitbulls</h2>

  <section class="principles-section">
    <article class="principle-card">
      <h3>üéØ Positive Reinforcement Protocol</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Mark the Behavior:</strong> Use clicker or "Yes!" at exact moment of correct behavior</li>
        <li><strong>Reward Immediately:</strong> Within 1-2 seconds of behavior</li>
        <li><strong>High-Value Rewards:</strong> Small, soft treats Gypsy loves (chicken, cheese, hot dogs)</li>
        <li><strong>Variable Reinforcement:</strong> Once learned, reward randomly to maintain reliability</li>
      </ul>
    </article>
  </section>

